sub_title: Actor, Entertainer, Creative Producer speaking fluently English, Dutch and Russian. Member of Equity UK and Spotlight UK.
summary:
Natalia De Coninck (Moscow 1990) moved soon after her birth to The Netherlands. She speaks fluently English (American and British), Dutch and Russian.

She is very creative; started as a young pianist, performed ballet and belly dancing, followed theatre classes and took everywhere creative challenges where she could find.
In 2013 she graduated for "Leisure & Hospitality Executive" in The Netherlands.
That year she started the study in Acting at the American Academy of Dramatic Arts in LA and she belongs to the Alumni of that conservatory. 
After that she was assistant program leader in a Girl Scouts camp in the Sierra Nevada and worked at Madame Tussauds in London for 5 months. There she got "The best employee of the month Award".
She continued her study in Acting and graduated at the Theatre of Arts in Hollywood (CA). She learned to speak fluently English and to work on a professional way for on the stage and in front of the camera. 
She wrote a one person show: «Believe» and it showed it was a great success, she played in several theatre pieces with real actors and she wrote the script for a short film, which was produced. She also studied (parallel) Advanced Conversation at the Mentor language institute in Westwood.
She performed as stand-up comedian at the Comedy Store in Hollywood (CA).
Actually she works at Dinerspel in The Netherlands as host for "Mystery Games" and she worked in the summer in 3 consecutive years in Italy as entertainer, actress and dancer for LikeIT Entertainment.

I want to bring love and happiness to people by playing in the theater, films or as entertainer. I feel a great sense of responsibility for my work and for people and this world. Working together in a close group to achieve this is my goal. Humor can bring some light in the darkness of the world.
